# Documentation Rules

## Philosophy

**Documentation First** — intent and context before code.

Every feature requires: **Context → Plan → Implementation → Review**.

## Workflow

```
Context → Plan → Build → Review → Document
```

| Stage | Location | Template |
|-------|----------|----------|
| Context | `docs/context/` | `templates/context-template.md` |
| Plan | `docs/plan/` | `templates/plan-template.md` |
| Build record | `docs/build/` | — |
| Review | PR or `docs/build/` | `templates/review-template.md` |
| Skills | `docs/skills/` | — |

## When Writing

- Use `templates/` — do not invent new document structures
- Include **Why**, **What**, and **Impact** in every significant doc
- Never store secrets or credential values in docs
- Link related docs (`PROJECT_VISION.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, Plan refs)

## Plan Gate

- No Build without an approved Plan in `docs/plan/`
- Record implementation results in `docs/build/` after Review
- Update `docs/context/` when glossary or constraints change

## Agent Handoff

- Planner → `docs/plan/` → Builder
- Builder → `docs/build/` → Reviewer → Documenter
- Follow `agents/Planner.md`, `agents/Documenter.md`
